  "explanation": "The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution of the stolen funds, demonstrating a degree of remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. However, embezzlement by a professional accountant represents a significant breach of fiduciary trust, which is a serious offense that requires a clear deterrent. Balancing the mitigating factors of a clean prior record and partial repayment against the aggravating factor of the breach of trust, a short period of incarceration is warranted, which is expected to be followed by a period of supervised probation and mandatory full restitution.",
